	M	framework/src/test/java/org/apache/felix/framework/ServiceRegistryTest.java&lt;br/&gt;
Committed r1778984&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Thx for the patch !&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16923049" author="rsabitov" created="Thu, 5 Sep 2019 04:59:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Same issue in Felix 6.0.3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;a check for usage count has gone from&#160;org.apache.felix.framework.ServiceRegistry#getServicesInUse&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Oh, I think I got it wrong. This issue was about usingBundles(), now the issue is with &quot;getServicesInUse&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Closing&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
